OL,3,CSheffield boy first youngster to be
OL,4,Cconvicted for encouraging self-harm
OL,5,Conline
OL,7,FA teenager has been convicted for
OL,8,Fencouraging self-harm online - the
OL,9,Ffirst of its kind in the country for a
OL,10,Fjuvenile.
OL,12,FSouth Yorkshire Police said the 17-
OL,13,Fyear-old boy from Sheffield sent
OL,14,Fthreatening and sinister online
OL,15,Fmessages to a vulnerable girl.
OL,17,FThe teenage victim, who is from
OL,18,Foutside the South Yorkshire area, was
OL,19,Fso frightened by the boy's messages
OL,20,Fthat she felt she had no choice but to
OL,21,Fdo as he said and self-harm.
